{
  "texts": [
    "This study proposes a novel approach that combines a K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) classifier with a Conditional Random Fields (CRF) model under a semi-supervised learning framework to improve the performance of NER on tweets.",
    "The goal is to leverage both coarse global evidence from similar tweets and fine-grained local contextual information to accurately recognize named entities in this challenging domain (Liu et al., 2011).",
    "The methodology introduced by Liu et al. (2011) is built on a hybrid system that integrates a KNN classifier with a CRF labeler.",
    "The KNN classifier is employed to gather global evidence across similar tweets by prelabeling entities based on their proximity to labeled data.",
    "The CRF model then takes over to capture more detailed, tweet-level contextual information."
  ]
}